@NODE Voraussetzungen "Requirements"

Hardware requirements
---------------------

MUINames requires an Amiga with OS3.0 or better because it uses some
systemfunctions that are not part of older OS-versions, i.e. memory-
pools.


MUINames needs @{"MUI" LINK MUI}. This must be installed before the
first start of MUINames.

A high level-processor or large amounts of RAM are not necessary.

A harddisk ist not required but highly recommended.

MUINames is a standalone-program that also works without MUIVideo.
The sense of the program gets clear in teamwork with MUIVideo. So the
requirements of @{"MUIVideo" LINK //Dokumentation/MUIVideo.guide/MAIN} are important, too.


@ENDNODE
@NODE Installation "Installation"

Installation of the program
---------------------------

To install the program copy the whole directory to your harddisk.
Assigns are not necessary.


Since version 2.20 of @{"MUIVideo" LINK //Dokumentation/MUIVideo.guide/MAIN} MUINames is part of the archive.
If you followed the instructions to install MUIVideo, MUINames is already
installed.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Start "Programstart etc."

Starting the program
--------------------

MUINames can be started in different ways:

1. Double click on the icon.

2. By typing "MUINames" in a shell.

Please look at the documentation to @{"MUIVideo" LINK //Dokumentation/MUIVideo.guide/MAIN} how to start an ARexx-program.

At this time MUINames does not accept any parameters or tooltypes.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Bedienung "Usage"

Using the program
-----------------

The window of MUINames consists of three parts: The first one is a group
of lists containing names. The look of them depends on the preferences
of MUI.

The second one is a line of switches for changes in the active list.
A description of these switches follows below.

The third one is another line of switches, their description also
follows below.

There are also some menus.


Functions of the switches:
--------------------------

New:

  Adds an entry to the active list.

Delete:

  Deletes the marked entry in the active list.

Up:

  Moves the marked entry one position up.

Down:

  Moves the marked entry one position down.

Sort:

  Sorts the active list by last names.

Save:

  Saves the active list.

Load:

  Loads the last saved version of the active list.

Anhängen:

Ersetzen:

ARexx:

Quit:

  Quits MUINames.

@ENDNODE
@NODE ARexx "ARexx..."

ARexx...:
---------

Clicking this button opens an requester in which you can choose an
ARexx-script to be executed.

As an alternative the scripts can be executed from MUIVideo. Both
programs can be run at the same time, you do not need to end MUINames
to continue your work in MUIVideo.


@ENDNODE
@NODE ARexxPort "The ARexx-port"

The Arexx-port of MUINames:
---------------------------

MUINames is an "add-on" for @{"MUIVideo" LINK //Dokumentation/MUIVideo.guide/MAIN}, so a big part
of their functionality consists of the communication between them.
This is done via the ARexx-port.

If you don`t know what ARexx is or how to use it, please read the
manual. This is part of the OS since Version 2.04.

Here are the descriptions of the ARexx-commands. MUINames also
understands the standard commands of every @{"MUI" LINK MUI}-program.
A description of these standard commands can be found in the
documentation of MUI and MUIVideo.

The commands are:

  @{" ABOUT  " LINK A_About}
  @{" APPEND " LINK A_Append}
  @{" CHANGE " LINK A_Change}
  @{" COPY   " LINK A_Copy}
  @{" COUNT  " LINK A_Count}
  @{" CUT    " LINK A_Cut}
  @{" DELETE " LINK A_Delete}
  @{" DOWN   " LINK A_Down}
  @{" FIND   " LINK A_Find}
  @{" GET    " LINK A_Get}
  @{" GOTO   " LINK A_Goto}
  @{" LOAD   " LINK A_Load}
  @{" NEW    " LINK A_New}
  @{" PAGE   " LINK A_Page}
  @{" PASTE  " LINK A_Paste}
  @{" SAVE   " LINK A_Save}
  @{" SET    " LINK A_Set}
  @{" SORT   " LINK A_Sort}
  @{" UP     " LINK A_Up}

@ENDNODE
